summary: This is an email chain from September 2021 regarding the discovery process in the Ghislaine Maxwell case. An FBI Special Agent from the New York Field Office is sending communications they had with victims, witnesses, and attorneys to the prosecution team, who are having technical issues opening a zipped file and request it be uploaded unzipped to a USAfx folder.

persons.name: Special Agent - FBI New York Field Office
persons.context: The sender of the initial email attaching communications they had with victims, witnesses, and attorneys. Works on the Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking desk.

events.title: FBI Agent Sends Discovery Communications
events.description: An FBI Special Agent sends a zip file containing their communications with victims, witnesses, and attorneys to the prosecution team as part of the discovery process in the Ghislaine Maxwell case.
personsInvolved: Special Agent - FBI New York Field Office

events.title: Prosecution Requests Unzipped Files
events.description: A member of the prosecution team emails the FBI agent stating the provided zip file is unopenable and requests the communications be sent unzipped via the USAfx system to a specific folder for the Maxwell case.

keyFacts: The document is part of the discovery process in United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (docket 3500).
An FBI Special Agent from the Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking desk in New York had communications with victims, witnesses, and attorneys relevant to the case.
The prosecution team experienced technical difficulties opening a zipped file containing these communications in September 2021.
The email chain shows logistical coordination between law enforcement and prosecutors regarding evidence handling.
The document reference EFTA00156237 is associated with the FBI agent's desk or file system.
